High Level Design

-> High level design or HLD is an intial step in the development of applications in which the overall structure of the system 
is planned. Mainly focuses on different components of the system work together without getting to know the internal code and 
implementation.  
-> Helps everyone in the project understand the requirements and ensures good communication during development.
-> Crucial for developers, architects and product managers because it allows them to make sure that all stakeholders
are align with the project objectives. Thats why it is called as Macro level design.

The most common request flow most applications follow from user to data and back.     ->1.1 data stores
users -> CDN/Edge -> Load balancers/API users CDN /Edge gateway -> 1.Application logic  -> 1.2 (1.3.1) Logs and metrics
                                                                  2. Identity/ access   -> 1.3 Asunc Queue & Workers 

Components of High level design:
================================
Understanding the components of high level design is inportant becauses that meets user needs and technical requirements.

1. System Architecture -> System architecture is an overview of the system that represents the structure and relationship between other components.
It helps to visually represent how different parts interact and function.

2. Modeuls and components -> High level design breaks down the system into modules or components each with specific roles and reponsibilities, 
and has distinct function that contributes to the entire system, helping in developing an efficient system.


